article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 85, Nicholls State 67
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. (AP) -- Marcus Clark scored a career-high 29 points as Stephen F. Austin defeated Southland Conference foe Nicholls State 85-67 Wednesday night. It was the third consecutive game in which Clark scored at least 20 points. The Lumberjacks (8-7, 2-2 Southland) led by 11 points at halftime, despite struggling at the free-throw line, shooting only 27 percent. But Clark and Josh Porter led Stephen F. Austin to a second-half offensive explosion as Porter finished the game with 19 points. The Lumberjacks went through a stretch in the second half that saw them connect on eight consecutive shots and hit 11-of-12, as the Lumberjacks extended their lead to 20 points. The Lumberjacks held Nicholls State (5-11, 0-5) to a 42 percent shooting performance and outrebounded the Colonels 35-33. Anthony Paez added 11 points for the Lumberjacks. B.J. Searles led Nicholls State with 17 points, while Shawn King added 13.
